# Tasks from 23 Oct 2020 
Topic: Correlation between crime rates and (factor 1) and (factor 2) in London and Singapore during xx-xx (time period) 

To do: 
  Figure out timeframe to use 
  Figure out the factors
  Figure out if the cities work 

things to think about: 
-the rationale: why these cities? why these variables? why this timeframe? -> rationale should bebased on literature review or hypothesis
-variables: they can come from a hypothesis stemming from common sense (i.e. proverty affects crime) or literature review 

-research question can be framed around:
1. comparing the different factors' influence on crime rates in 2 cities 
2. by looking at these 2 cities as case studies coming to conlclusions arounf which factors influence crime rates


## Data sources

Cities:
- London: 
https://data.london.gov.uk/dataset/recorded_crime_summary  --> crime rate/borough
https://www.met.police.uk/sd/stats-and-data/met/crime-data-dashboard/ --> crime rate by month (also colour codes by borough!! its quite cool) 
https://www.kaggle.com/jboysen/london-crime
https://www.statista.com/topics/4627/crime-in-london/ --> crime rates (yearly)
https://data.london.gov.uk/dataset/recorded_crime_associated  --> associated factors to crime
https://data.london.gov.uk/dataset/public-perception- --> Public perception of police
https://data.london.gov.uk/dataset/daily-areal-rainfall --> Daily rainfall of differents areas (2018)
https://www.google.com/search?client=safari&rls=en&sxsrf=ALeKk034Y2YcDrVTHmYHXYzDKKJX1ZyK_g%3A1603683860556&ei=FEaWX8OlIfvAz7sPyMiAoAE&q=london+monthly+weather&oq=london+monthly+weather&gs_lcp=CgZwc3ktYWIQAzICCAAyBggAEAcQHjIGCAAQBxAeMgYIABAHEB4yBggAEAcQHjIGCAAQBxAeMgYIABAHEB4yBggAEAcQHjICCAAyBAgAEB46BAgAEEdQ3uYKWI3sCmDy7QpoAHAFeACAAT-IAc0CkgEBNpgBAKABAaoBB2d3cy13aXrIAQjAAQE&sclient=psy-ab&ved=0ahUKEwjD_9v2q9HsAhV74HMBHUgkABQQ4dUDCAw&uact=5
--> monthly temperatures of London

- New York:
https://www.kaggle.com/adamschroeder/crimes-new-york-city  --> Crime rate+ population/borough (2016)
https://data.world/mithragoesdark/crime-in-new-york-city --> Crimes per borough (2014-2015)
https://www.labor.ny.gov/stats/nyc/ --> Employment per borough
https://www.kaggle.com/selfishgene/historical-hourly-weather-data  --> City's weather attributes (pressure, temperature...) over same period

- Tokyo:
https://www.kaggle.com/loovmj/tokyo-weather-data  --> Weather data of Tokyo (2018)
https://knoema.com/atlas/Japan/Tokyo/datasets --> some data on Tokyo including the crime rate
https://www.google.com/search?client=safari&rls=en&sxsrf=ALeKk03_oRlYJlMPo8nm67osgpJhEBh9tw%3A1603683797375&ei=1UWWX625FsbXz7sP_MuNyAE&q=tokyo+monthly+weather+&oq=tokyo+monthly+weather+&gs_lcp=CgZwc3ktYWIQAzIFCAAQyQMyAggAMgYIABAWEB4yBggAEBYQHjoECAAQRzoHCCMQsAIQJzoICCEQFhAdEB5Qlh5Y3zRg0DZoAHABeACAAU-IAaEEkgECMTCYAQCgAQGqAQdnd3Mtd2l6yAEIwAEB&sclient=psy-ab&ved=0ahUKEwjt98vYq9HsAhXG63MBHfxlAxkQ4dUDCAw&uact=5 
--> tokyo monthly temperature (the've got 4 seasons too though, temperature is similar to london and may not be particulalry useful) 

- Singapore:
https://data.gov.sg/dataset/overall-crime-cases-crime-rate?resource_id=124af3cd-08d5-405a-9c83-02f0ad16cb5f  --> crime rate (classified)
https://data.gov.sg/dataset/realtime-weather-readings --> Weather readings (temperature, wind...)(2016)

- Hong Kong:
https://www.police.gov.hk/ppp_en/09_statistics/csd.html --> data on Hong Kong crime rate by month (Oct 2019- Sep 2020)
https://data.gov.hk/en-data/dataset/hk-hkpf-stat-crm-stat-detail/resource/1708d8c2-11f5-4f9e-9a11-31bd599efcb2 --> crime rate data over last 10 years
https://www.kaggle.com/rameessahlu/hong-kong-rain-fall --> hong kong rainfall  
https://www.google.com/search?client=safari&rls=en&sxsrf=ALeKk00R7y0v0OrMNLkTW_Lsjvb7di-vyQ%3A1603684039206&ei=x0aWX-2ODJjaz7sP-Ju4-AQ&q=hong+kong+monthly+weather&oq=hong+kong+monthly+weather&gs_lcp=CgZwc3ktYWIQAzIGCAAQBxAeMgIIADICCAAyBAgAEB4yBggAEAgQHjIGCAAQCBAeMgYIABAIEB46BAgAEEc6CAgAEAgQBxAeUJ0VWOAjYOIkaAFwA3gAgAFDiAH9A5IBAjEwmAEAoAEBqgEHZ3dzLXdpesgBCMABAQ&sclient=psy-ab&ved=0ahUKEwitjvTLrNHsAhUY7XMBHfgNDk8Q4dUDCAw&uact=5
--> hong kong monthly temperature 

- US: 
https://www.governing.com/gov-data/safety-justice/crime-data-statistics-for-cities-local-law-enforcement-by-month.html --> crime rates by month (many different cities available)
Houston: https://www.houstontx.gov/police/cs/Monthly_Crime_Data_by_Street_and_Police_Beat.htm --> crime rat eby month (2019-2020)
